  "summary": "A wide plywood dresser with four full-width drawers, 2x2 legs, and side/top trim — a straightforward drawer stack rather than a mixed drawer-and-shelf design.",
  "description": "The carcass is two plywood sides joined by a top, a bottom support, and a plywood back, standing on four 2x2 legs — a genuinely large case, so keep the sides and legs square as you assemble, since a 4-drawer stack this wide shows any lean immediately. Side and top trim finish the visible plywood edges.\n\n**All four drawers are the same width**, running the full interior of the case — there's no mixed shelf-and-drawer layout here, just a straightforward stack. Save the scrap piece from the back panel to use as one drawer's bottom, which is a real material saving on a build this size.\n\nBuild each drawer box from 1x6 sides, front, and back, with a 1x8 drawer face that must be a true 7-1/4\" wide board — call this out specifically when buying material, since a narrower nominal 1x8 will leave a visible gap between drawer faces.",
